---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms | CrossCoders" description="The terms for using the CrossCoders website and engaging our services.">
  <PageHero eyebrow="Legal" title="Terms." cta={false} />
  <section class="psec">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p style="color:var(--ink-mute)">Last updated: 24 June 2026. A plain-English summary — your project's full engagement terms are agreed in writing before we start.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Using this site</h2>
      <p>The content and design of this site are ours. Please don’t copy or reuse them without permission. The site is provided “as is”.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Our work together</h2>
      <p>Project scope, estimates, payment terms and ownership are agreed in writing before we start. On full payment, the software and design we build for you are yours.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Third-party costs</h2>
      <p>Domains, hosting, premium tools and similar third-party costs are billed separately or paid by you directly, as agreed.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Care plans</h2>
      <p>Ongoing care is a separate, optional arrangement with its own terms — no unlimited edits, and larger custom work is quoted separately.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Donations</h2>
      <p>Gifts through this site are voluntary and processed securely by Paystack. They support the Kingdom Come Foundation's free and subsidised builds for under-resourced churches, and are applied at our reasonable discretion — or toward a specific build you choose. The Foundation is in formation, so gifts are <b>not yet tax-deductible</b>. Donations are generally non-refundable; if something went wrong with a gift, email <a href="mailto:daniel@crosscoders.co.za" style="color:var(--forest-deep)">daniel@crosscoders.co.za</a> and we'll put it right.</p>
      <h2 class="serif">Governing law</h2>
      <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of South Africa.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
